  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\n```\r\n{\r\nfor { let i_0 := 0 } lt(i_0, 0x60) { i_0 := add(i_0, 0x20) } {\r\nfunction foo_noreturn_0() {}\r\n}\r\nfoo_noreturn_0()\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n`solc` tells me this is not valid yul code, but should it be that way?\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ solc --strict-assembly <code.yul>\r\ncode.yul:5:1: Error: Function not found.\r\nfoo_noreturn_0()\r\n^------------^\r\n```",
